rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
A type containing people who are members of a chivalric orders, i.e. people who are knights or ladies/dames. This type includes members of active and inactive, medieval and modern legitimate orders of chivalry.
Persons who are members of a chivalric order:
## Members of monarchical chivalric orders such as Order of the Thistle and Order of the Dragon (e.g. James Hamilton, 6th Duke of Hamilton, Stefan Lazarevi??).
## Members of military chivalric orders such as Knights Templar and Teutonic Knights (e.g. Geoffroy de Charney, Archduke Anton).
## Members of religious chivalric orders such as Order of St. Gregory the Great and Order of the Golden Spur (e.g. Robert J. Lane, Julius Caesar Scaliger).
## Members of orders founded by noblemen such as the Order of St. Catherine and Order of the Crescent (e.g. Princess Alice, Charles Marsh Schomberg).
## Members of modern chivalric orders that confer knighthood such as the Order of the Elephant and Order of the British Empire (e.g. Maha Vajiralongkorn, Abdullah I of Jordan, Timothy Granville-Chapman).
## Female members of chivalric orders (e.g. Alexandra of Denmark, Beatrix of the Netherlands, Alexandra Hasluck).
Persons who are NOT members of chivalric orders:
## Noble persons who are not members of any order of chivalry (e.g. James Francis Edward Stuart, Anna Kaiulani, Frances Stevenson). In these cases use mso:royalty.noble_person.
## Knights who are not members of any organized order of chivalry (e.g. Charles Cornwallis, 2nd Baron Cornwallis, Sir Alexander Stevenson, Stephen Fox).
## Ladies and dames who are not members of any organized order of chivalry (e.g. Lady Elizabeth Stanley, Lady Louise Windsor).
Founders of chivalric orders (e.g. Charles I of Hungary, Napoleon I of France, Selim III) Use the Chivalric order founder type for these.
## Members of false, illegitimate, unrecognized or self-styled orders (e.g. Mar Samuel, Juliusz Nowina-Sokolnicki).
## Members of non-chivalric religious and monastic orders such as Dominican Order and Community of the Resurrection (e.g. Guillaume Courtet, Walter Frere).
## Recipients of orders not pertaining to societies and fellowships of knights such as orders of merit and similar awards. (e.g. Order of British India recipient Hashim Ali Khan, Distinguished Service Order recipient Arnold Jackson).

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
A society or fellowship of knights and/or dames/ladies based on the military orders of the Crusades.
Things that are an order of chivalry:
## Monarchical chivalric orders (e.g. Order of the Thistle, Order of the Dragon, Order of the Garter, Order of the Crown).
## Military chivalric orders (e.g. Knights Templar, Teutonic Knights, Order of Alcantara).
## Religious chivalric orders (e.g. Order of the Holy Sepulchre, Order of St. Gregory the Great, Order of the Golden Spur).
## Orders founded by noblemen (e.g. Order of St. Catherine, Order of the Crescent, Order of Saint Hubert).
## Modern chivalric orders (e.g. Order of the Elephant, Order of the British Empire, Order of Australia, Royal Norwegian Order of Merit).
Things that are NOT an order of chivalry:
## Pseudo-chivalric orders or self-styled order (e.g. Order of the Collar of Saint Agatha, Sovereign Military and Hospitalier Order of St. John of Jerusalem, Niadh Nask).
## Non-chivalric orders such as orders of merit and military awards (e.g. Distinguished Service Order, Order of Saint Barbara, Tom???? Garrigue Masaryk Order, Federal Cross of Merit). Use mso:award.award in these cases.
## Non-chivalric religious and monastic orders (e.g. Dominican Order, Order of Poor Ladies, Chishti Order, Order of Saint Benedict (Orthodox)). In these cases use mso:religion.religious_order.
## Fraternal and professional organizations (e.g. Royal Antediluvian Order of Buffaloes, International Order of Twelve Knights and Daughters of Tabor, Order of Engineers, Friends of the Western Buddhist Order). In these cases use mso:organization.organization.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A set of ranks and associated privileges that are granted to the residents of a particular territory, generally on the basis of heredity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: System of Nobility

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a system of nobility to a country where the system operates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country of Origin

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a system of nobility to information about which orders of chivalry are recognized by the system of nobility (and when they were recognized).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orders of Chivalry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates system of nobility to another system of nobility that supercedes it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Superceded by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a system of nobility to an earlier system of nobility which was replaced by the first system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Supercedes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a system of nobility to information about noble ranks granted and recognized by the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a system of nobility to information about noble titles granted and recognized by the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Titles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a system of nobility to the date on which the system came into being.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Used from Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a system of nobility to the date on which the system officially came to an end.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Used to Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the chivalric orders that are recognized by a system of nobility and when they are recognized.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: System-Order Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the system of nobility first recognized the order of chivalry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the given chivalric order.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Order

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the system of nobility that uses the given order of chivalry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: System of Nobility

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the system of nobility last recognized the order of chivalry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the ranks that are recognized by a system of nobility and when they are recognized.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: System-Rank Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the system of nobility first recognized the rank.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the given rank.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rank

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the given system of nobility.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the system of nobility last recognized the rank.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the titles that are recognized by a system of nobility and when they are recognized.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: System-Title Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the system of nobility first recognized the title.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the monarch who created the title within the given system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Monarch

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the given system of nobility.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the given title.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Title

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date that the system of nobility last recognized the title.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To Date
